revision.text:
{{Infobox News event |image= |caption= |date= January 20, 2006 |time=08:30 local time (11:30 UTC) |place=[[Copiapó]], [[Chile]] |casualties1= 2 killed |casualties2= 2 Injured }} The '''2006 Copiapó mining accident''' occurred on January 20, 2006, when an explosion occurred in the underground Carola-Agustina copper mine in [[Copiapó]], [[Chile]] after two trucks collided, covering the only escape route for the miners inside the mine.<ref name="esmas"/><ref name="cooperativa">{{Cite web |url= http://www.cooperativa.cl/p4_noticias/site/artic/20060120/pags/20060120111455.html |title=Accidente en mina de Atacama deja a cerca de 70 trabajadores atrapados - Cooperativa.cl |publisher=[[Radio Cooperativa]] |accessdate=29 August 2010 |date=20 January 2006 |language=es}}</ref>
The explosion caused two deaths and two injuries. 70 miners were trapped.<ref name="esmas">{{Cite web |url = http://www.esmas.com/noticierostelevisa/internacionales/505551.html |title = Explosión en mina en Chile deja dos muertos |work = EsMas.com |accessdate = 29 August 2010 |date = 20 January 2006 |language = es |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20101021081715/http://www.esmas.com/noticierostelevisa/internacionales/505551.html |archive-date = 2010-10-21 |dead-url = yes |df = }}</ref>
Shortly after the explosion occurred, workers at the nearby mine, "Punta de Cobre", began digging a tunnel towards the Carola-Agustina mine to assist in rescuing the trapped miners.<ref name="esmas"/>
Rescue efforts lasted seven hours, and the trapped miners were rescued alive.
