{{Motorsport season |series = European Truck Racing Championship |link = European Truck Racing Championship |year = 2007 }}
The '''2007 FIA European Truck Racing Championship''' was a multi-event motor racing championship for production based trucks held across Europe. The championship features a mix of professional motor racing teams and privately funded amateur drivers competing in highly modified versions of two-axle [[tractor unit]]s which conform to the technical regulations for the championship. It was the 23rd European Truck Racing Championship season and began at [[Circuit de Catalunya|Catalunya]] on April 1, with the finale at [[Circuito del Jarama|Jarama]] on October 7 after nine events. The championship was won by [[Markus Bösiger]], taking his first title.
