{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}} {{Use Australian English|date=August 2015}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Cygnet Folk Festival | native_name = | native_name_lang = | logo = | logo_alt = | logo_caption = | logo_size = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | status = Active | genre = [[Folk festival]] | date = | begins ={{start date|df=y|2018|01|12}} | ends = {{start date|df=y|2018|01|14}} | frequency = 2nd weekend in January | venue = | location = {{TAScity|Cygnet}}, [[Tasmania]] | coordinates = {{coord|43|09|00|S|147|04|12|E|type:event|display=inline,title}} | country = Australia | years_active = {{age|1982|01|12}} | first = {{start date|df=y|1982|01}} | founder_name = The Huon Folk Inc Management Committee | last = <!-- Date of most recent event; if the event will not be held again, use {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD|df=y}} --> | prev = {{start date|df=y|2016|01}} | next = {{start date|df=y|2017|01|06}} | participants = 400{{endash}}500 musicians | attendance = 6,000 | capacity = | area = | budget = | activity = | leader_name = Huon Folk Inc | patron = | organised = <!-- "organized=" also works --> | filing = | people = | member = | sponsor = | website = {{URL|cygnetfolkfestival.org/}} | footnotes = <ref name=merc2015/> }} The '''Cygnet Folk Festival''' is a three-day [[folk music]] festival held in [[Cygnet, Tasmania|Cygnet]] in [[Tasmania]], Australia, that is held annually on the second weekend in January.<ref name=merc2015>{{cite web| url=http://www.themercury.com.au/entertainment/thousands-to-converge-on-tassie-town-for-33rd-annual-cygnet-folk-festival/story-fnj3tycr-1227178340852|title=Thousands to converge on Tassie town for 33rd annual Cygnet Folk Festival|work=[[The Mercury (Hobart)|The Mercury]] |location=Hobart |date=8 January 2015 |accessdate=3 August 2015 |author=Young, Kane}}</ref>
The festival has developed as one of the premier cultural events in Tasmania's arts calendar. Every year on the second weekend in January, the small village of Cygnet, situated in the [[Huon Valley]] in the bay of Port Cygnet, presents a variety of music, dance, and related arts, over three days. Performances take place in the pubs, halls, cafes, churches, parks and streets of Cygnet. The festival allows for a range of concerts, workshops, master classes, poetry reading, youth awards, children's events, gourmet food stalls featuring local produce, sessions, arts and crafts market and dances. The program features an eclectic mix of artists including local Tasmanians, mainland Australians and international guests.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tasmanianartsguide.com.au/whats-on/festivals/cygnet-folk-festival/ |title=Cygnet Folk Festival |work=Tasmanian Arts Guide |date=2015 |accessdate=3 August 2015 }}</ref>
Some of the well-known festival headline acts over the years include [[Riley Lee]], [[Afenginn]],<ref name=merc2015/> [[My Friend the Chocolate Cake]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://timberandsteel.wordpress.com/2011/10/31/30th-cygnet-folk-festival-announces-artist-lineup/ |title=30th Cygnet Folk Festival Announces Artist Lineup |work=Timber and Steel |date=31 October 2011 |author=Winton, Andrew |accessdate=3 August 2015 }}</ref> [[Stiff Gins]], [[Zulya Kamalova]], [[Rory McLeod (singer-songwriter)|Rory McLeod]] and [[Frank Yamma]].
