{{Infobox wildfire | title = Empire Fire (2017) | image = File:2017 08 08-19.36.10.643-CDT.jpg | caption = Empire Fire on August 8, 2017 | cost = | injuries = | fatalities = | reference =<ref name=InciWeb>{{cite web|title=Empire Fire|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/5475/|website=Empire Fire|publisher=National Park Service|date=27 November 2017|accessdate=6 December 2017}}</ref> <!-- ONLY FOR INDIVIDUAL FIRES --> | date = {{Start date|2017|8|1}} – {{End date|2017|11|27}} | location = [[Yosemite National Park]], [[California]], [[United States]] | coordinates = {{coord|37.644| -119.618|display=inline,title}} | pushpin_map = USA California Northern | pushpin_map_caption = Location of fire in California. | area = {{Convert|8,094|acre|km2|0}} | buildings = | cause = Lightning/Natural | landuse = | perps = | motive = }} The '''Empire Fire''' was a wildfire that burned in [[Yosemite National Park]] in [[California]] in the [[United States]]. The fire was reported on August 1, 2017 and was caused by lightning. It burned {{Convert|8,094|acre|km2|0}}, before it was fully contained on November 27. The fire affected recreational activities in the national park.
==The fire==
The Empire Fire was reported on August 1, 2017 at 8:45 AM. It is located east of [[Badger Pass Ski Area]] and next to [[Bridalveil Creek Campground]] in [[Yosemite National Park]]. The fire was naturally caused, possibly by [[lightning]]. It was fueled by [[red fir]] timber, dormant brush, green leaf [[manzanita]], chinquapan brush, and dead and down material.<ref name=InciWeb/>
On November 27, the fire was reported to be 100% contained.<ref name="InciWeb" />
