{{Infobox pro wrestling championship | championshipname=''Pequeño Reyes del Aire'' | image = Pierothito pressing Tzuki.jpg | image_size =200px | caption = [[Pierrothito]] pressing [[Tsuki]], both have competed in the Pequeños Reyes del Aire tournaments | currentholder=[[Electrico (wrestler)|Eléctrico]]<ref name=PRdA2014/><ref name=FuegoPRdA2014/> | won=January 5, 2014<ref name=PRdA2014/><ref name=FuegoPRdA2014/> | promotion=[[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] | created=July 13, 2007<ref name=PequenoReyes07/> | mostreigns=[[Pequeño Black Warrior]] (2)<ref name=PequenoReyes09/> | firstchamp=[[Pequeño Damián 666]]<ref name=PequenoReyes07/> | oldest= | youngest=[[Mascarita Dorada]] {{nobr|(25 years, 319 days)}} | heaviest=Pequeño Damián 666/Demus 3:16 ({{convert|80|kg|lb|abbr=on}})<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first --> | lightest= Mascarita Dorada ({{convert|50|kg|lb|abbr=on}})<!--In Mexico they measure weight in kilograms so that should be first --> }} The '''''Pequeño Reyes del Aire''''' Tournament ([[Spanish language|Spanish]] for the "Little Kings of the Air") is an annual wrestling tournament promoted by the Mexican professional wrestling promotion [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] (CMLL) and has been held since 2007, holding two tournaments in 2012, and one every other year. The tournament includes a varying number of wrestlers, competing in a ''[[Torneo cibernetico]]'' match, essentially a multi-man elimination match with the last competitor remaining is declared that year's ''Pequeño Rey del Aire'' and is given a trophy. The match is based on CMLL's ''[[CMLL Reyes del Aire|Reyes del Aire]]'' tournament which has an identical purpose, format and award. The winner is not normally awarded with a match for the [[CMLL World Mini-Estrella Championship]] or the [[Mexican National Lightweight Championship]], the two Mini-Estrellas championships that CMLL promotes, as a direct result of their tournament victory but has as times been used to build but either a championship match or [[narrative thread|storylines]] between rival wrestlers.
There has been a total of ten tournaments held as of January 2015, with nine different winners, only [[Pequeño Black Warrior]] has won the tournament twice.<ref name=PequenoReyes>{{cite web | url=http://www.prowrestlinghistory.com/supercards/mexico/emll/Pequeño.html | title= Pequeño Reyes del Aire | accessdate= September 29, 2014 | publisher= Pro Wrestling History}}</ref> A total of 27 Mini-Estrellas have appeared in the nine tournaments held so far, two wrestlers have appeared in eight of the ''Pequeños Reyes del Aire'', [[Pequeño Olímpico]] and [[Demus 3:16|Pequeño Damián 666 / Demus 3:16]]. Demus 3:16 has the most eliminations, with nine while [[Último Dragoncito]] has eliminated 9 men. Only 4 men have competed without eliminating a single opponent [[Fire (wrestler)|Fire]], [[Mini Maximo]], [[Sombrita]] and [[Stukita]].<ref group=Note>The statistics are supported by the source for each individual tournament.</ref> [[Mascarita Dorada]] is the youngest tournament winner ever, at 25 years of age when he won the [[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire (2008)|2008 tournament]] while [[Fantasy (Mini-Estrella)|Fantasy]] is the youngest competitor ever, 18 years old when he entered the [[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire (2007)|2007 tournament]]. Pequeño Black Warrior is the oldest tournament winner, he was 42 years old when he won the [[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire 2012 (Guadalajara)|2012 Guadalajara tournament]], while [[Pierrothito]] was 46 years old when he competed in the [[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire (2014)|2014 tournament]] making him the oldest competitor overall.
