==Pequeños Reyes del Aire 2012 (Guadalajara)== {{Infobox wrestling event |name=''Pequeños Reyes del Aire'' (2012 Guadalajara) |image=LuchaLibreObrera022.JPG |caption=[[Demus 3:16]] and [[Shockercito]], participants in the Guadalajara version of the tournament. |promotion = [[Consejo Mundial de Lucha Libre]] |date=May 1, 2012 |attendance= |venue=Arena Coliseo, Guadalajara |city = [[Guadalajara, Jalisco]], [[Mexico]] |liveevent=Y |lastevent=''[[CMLL Reyes del Aire#CMLL Reyes del Aire 2012 Guadalajara|Reyes del Aire]]'' (2012) |nextevent=''[[CMLL Mini-Estrellas Tournaments#Mini-Estrella Infierno en el Ring 2012|Mini-Estrella Infierno en el Ring]]'' (2012) |event=''Pequeños Reyes del Aire'' |lastevent2=''[[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire (2012)|Pequeños Reyes del Aire]]'' (2012 Mexico City) |nextevent2=''[[#Pequeños Reyes del Aire (2013)|Pequeños Reyes del Aire]]'' (2013) }} CMLL held a second '''''Pequeños Reyes del Aire''''' in 2012, this time in Arena Coliseo in [[Guadalajara]], [[Jalisco]], [[Mexico]] on October 30, 2012. The tournament format was the traditional ''torneo cibernetico'' where the ''tecnico'' team of [[Aereo (wrestler)|Aereo]], [[Astral (wrestler)|Astral]], [[Fantasy (Mini-Estrella)|Fantasy]], [[Pequeño Halcón]], [[Shockercito]] and [[Último Dragóncito]] faced off against the ''rudo'' team of [[Demus 3:16]], [[Mercurio (wrestler)|Mercurio]], [[Pequeño Black Warrior]], [[Pequeño Olímpico]], [[Pequeño Violencia]] and [[Pierrothito]]. During the match Shockercito hurt himself on a dive. Pequeño Black Warrior won the match to become the first man to ever win two ''Pequeños Reyes del Aire'' tournaments.<ref name=PeqReyesGuadalajara>{{cite web | url=http://www.fuegoenelring.com/articles_luchas_full.php?articles_id=3444 | title=LA TERCIA SENSACIÓN SIGUE SIENDO DE NIVEL MUNDIAL | date=October 31, 2012 | accessdate= November 1, 2012 | work=Fuego en el Ring | language=Spanish}}</ref> The 12 Mini-Estrellas involved in the tournament would face off again a week later inside a [[steel cage match]], contested under ''[[Lucha libre#Luchas de Apuestas|Luchas de Apuestas]]'' ("Bet match") where everyone will risk either their mask or their hair.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mediotiempo.com/mas-deportes/lucha-libre/noticias/2012/10/31/minis-del-cmll-a-la-jaula | title= Minis del CMLL a la jaula | date=October 31, 2012 | accessdate=October 31, 2012 | author=Redaccion MEDIOTIEMPO | work=MedioTiempo | language=Spanish}}</ref>
